Class SubscribeGroup

java.lang.Object
  org.phoenixbioinformatics.proxy.model.SubscribeGroup
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class SubscribeGroup
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

A Faces managed bean that manages the model information for a group of TAIR users being subscribed at once for a discount.

Author:
Robert J. Muller

registerAndSubscribeAllMembers

public java.lang.String registerAndSubscribeAllMembers(org.tair.bs.community.PersonDelegate delegate,
                                                       java.lang.String product)
Register and subscribe all members. You must verify all preconditions before calling this method. If there is a problem with a subscription, the process stops, but all subscribed and registered users remain subscribed and registered. Any problem with a member subscription marks that subscription as in error.

Parameters:
delegate - the business delegate
product - the name of the product
Returns:
the page to which to navigate

getSubscribingPi

private org.tair.bs.community.BsPerson getSubscribingPi()
Get the subscribing PI. The person id becomes the pointer to the subscribing person in the TAIR database. Note: this is a person, not a community. If the subscribing PI is a new registration, the person id will come back as null; the method also sets the autorenew status and the institution name for such a PI, as they are using the first record that was created before those options were set by the user.

Returns:
a person id
